paragraphs.title: 1. create dataset
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

import numpy as np

# create dataset
x_train = np.random.random((1000, 12))
y_train = np.random.randint(2, size=(1000, 1))
x_test = np.random.random((100, 12))
y_test = np.random.randint(2, size=(100, 1))

paragraphs.title: 1-1. show dataset
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plot_x = x_train[:, 0]
plot_y = x_train[:, 1]
plot_color = y_train.reshape(1000, )

plt.scatter(plot_x, plot_y, c=plot_color)
plt.show()

paragraphs.title: 2. create model
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.layers import Activation, Dense

# model = Sequential()
# model.add(Dense(1, input_dim=12, activation='sigmoid'))

# DNN model
model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(64, input_dim=12, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(64, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))

paragraphs.title: 5. show learning process
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

fig, loss_ax = plt.subplots()
acc_ax = loss_ax.twinx()

loss_ax.set_ylim([0.0, 1.0])
acc_ax.set_ylim([0.0, 1.0])

loss_ax.plot(hist.history['loss'], 'y', label='train loss')
acc_ax.plot(hist.history['acc'], 'b', label='train acc')

loss_ax.set_xlabel('epoch')
loss_ax.set_ylabel('loss')
acc_ax.set_ylabel('accuracy')

loss_ax.legend(loc='upper left')
acc_ax.legend(loc='lower left')

plt.show()

paragraphs.title: 6. evaluate model
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

loss_and_metrics = model.evaluate(x_test, y_test, batch_size=32)
print('loss_and_metrics:', loss_and_metrics)
